# AI Crypto Advisor MVP Standards

## Mission Focus
- Build a personalized crypto investor dashboard with:
  - Login/Signup
  - First-login onboarding quiz
  - Daily dashboard with Market News, Coin Prices, AI Insight, and Meme
  - User feedback (thumbs up/down) stored for future recommendations
- Prioritize shipping a working MVP in 1-2 work days.
- Execute in roadmap order from `docs/roadmap.md` (Phase 0 -> Phase 7).

## Technical Stack (Required)
- Frontend: React.
- Backend: Python Flask.
- Database: SQLite.
- Keep architecture modular so external providers can be swapped later with minimal refactor.
- Python setup must use a project-local virtual environment (`.venv`).

## Engineering Constraints
- Write unit tests and e2e tests for new or changed behavior.
- Ensure all tests pass before proposing completion.
- Keep code and folder structure clean; do not create unnecessary files or folders.
- Add new files, folders, and methods only when needed for clean architecture and design.
- Keep method names in simple English.
- Build in small slices suitable for weaker models:
  - One slice = one responsibility, usually up to 5 touched files.
  - Define exact file paths and API contracts before implementing.
  - Add at least one explicit acceptance test per slice.

## Workflow Rules
- Follow `.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc`: phase branch per phase, TODO branch per slice, auto-merge TODO→phase after tests, ask before phase→master.
- After every big change, ask the user for permission before committing.
- Save gotcha moments (important pitfalls, edge cases, or integration caveats) in project notes.
- For backend tasks, create and activate `.venv` before install/run/test commands.

## Product Scope Guardrails
- Prefer free-tier/public services and include fallback behavior when external APIs fail.
- Use only free public APIs and free-tier AI tools.
- Implement essentials first; defer non-MVP enhancements unless explicitly requested.
- Keep UX clean and readable over premature optimization.
- Prioritize readable code and good structure in every feature.
- Backend and logic generation should favor GPT-5.5 prompts.
- UI generation should favor Composer with contract-first prompts (states + props + API shape).

## Skill Evolution Rule
- Create project skills on the run when recurring work appears (for example: adding a new AI tool or replacing the meme provider).
